18/12/2002
ROME, Italy -- Visiting the Vatican on Tuesday (17 December), Croatian Deputy Prime Minister Goran Granic said the government will sign an agreement with religious communities by the end of the week, regulating relations between state institutions, the Serb Orthodox Church and the Islamic community.
Granic says the agreement will follow a model recommended by Pope John Paul II.
(HINA, HRT -- 17/12/02)
